  
                    
                        
                
                
            Lions fly-half Johnny Sexton has signed a new deal with the Irish Rugby Football Union that means he will play for Ireland and Leinster until 2021.Sexton, 33, was named 2018 World Rugby player of the year after helping Ireland to a Six Nations Grand Slam.The two-time British and Irish Lions back was contracted with the IRFU until the end of the 2019 Rugby World Cup.
    
        
"It is where I have always wanted to play so I am delighted to extend," said the Dublin-born player."We get looked after extremely well here and it is an exciting time for Irish rugby. I am looking forward to hopefully being a part of that over the next few years."
 
